@Node "Introduction" "IconAppearer.guide/Introduction"

Introduction

IconAppearer was designed to improve the consistency of the Workbench.
It tries to notify the Workbench when icons are changed, created,
deleted or renamed. For example while unpacking an LHA-archive
you can watch the icons appear on the Workbench if the appropriate
window is open.

IconAppearer uses a private workbench function so it's a hack.
Use it at your own risk. Anyway: on my system and those of my
betatesters, it is running stable.

@EndNode

@Node "System requirements" "IconAppearer.guide/System requirements"

System requirements        

"IconAppearer" needs OS 3.0 (V39) to operate
Higher and lower versions seem to work but it's a hack so there's no
real guarantee.

@EndNode

